wn%20arenas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20women%20have%20made%20significant%2C%20if%20uneven%2C%20gains%20in%20the%20corporate%20workforce.%20Women%20now%20make%20up%2010.4%25%20of%20CEOs%20at%20Fortune%20500%20companies%2C%20up%20from%20just%204.6%25%20in%202015.%20The%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20this%20small%20group%20is%20white.%20Women%20are%20now%20outpacing%20men%20in%20becoming%20entrepreneurs%3B%20today%20they%20own%20nearly%2039%25%20of%20American%20businesses%2C%20increasing%20the%20number%20of%20women-led%20companies%20by%2013.6%25%20between%202019%20and%202023%2C%20a%202024%20Wells%20Fargo%20report%20said.%20Firms%20owned%20by%20men%20grew%20by%20just%207%25%20in%20the%20same%20time%20period.%20In%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20however%2C%20Zuckerberg's%20%26quot%3Bmasculine%20energy%26quot%3B%20quip%20doesn't%20track%20with%20reality.%20As%20of%202022%2C%20women%20made%20up%20just%2022%25%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-ageism-tech-jobs-gen-z-boomers-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etech%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20the%20same%20proportion%20of%20jobs%20they%20held%20in%202005%2C%20the%20year%20after%20Facebook%20was%20founded.%20Women%20accounted%20for%2016%25%20of%20first-time%20VC-backed%20entrepreneurs%20and%20only%209%25%20of%20entrepreneurs%20who%20get%20VC-backing%20for%20two%20startups%2C%20according%20to%20a%202024%20paper%20that%20looked%20at%20aggregate%20data%20from%20Pitchbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20promises%20of%20the%20girlboss%20era%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20have%20come%20up%20short.%20In%20the%202010s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsheryl-sandberg-lean-in-complicated-legacy-holds-lesson-on-diversity-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESheryl%20Sandberg%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20on%20ambitious%20women%20to%20%26quot%3Blean%20in.%26quot%3B%20Work%20hard%20enough%2C%20assert%20yourself%2C%20and%20you%20can%20have%20it%20all.%20But%20the%20girlboss%20was%20an%20empty%20caricature%2C%20idolizing%20women%20who'd%20squeezed%20their%20way%20into%20the%20C-suite%20while%20trying%20old%20leadership%20tactics%20and%20wearing%20high%20heels.%20They%20were%20feminine%20and%20white%2C%20often%20thin%20and%20privileged.%20And%2C%20as%20Michelle%20Obama%20famously%20said%20of%20%26quot%3Bleaning%20in%26quot%3B%20in%202018%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20shit%20doesn't%20work%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20sprinkling%20of%20female%20founders%20and%20executives%20in%20a%20world%20run%20by%20men%20hasn't%20transformed%20it%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-jones-cookware-founders-tishgart-moelis-falling-out-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EToxic%20workplaces%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20still%20emerged%20at%20several%20women-led%20companies.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faway-steph-korey-apology-toxic-company-culture-report-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESteph%20Korey%20of%20Away%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20outed%20as%20a%20Slack%20bully%20(she%20apologized).%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-glossier-employees-allege-mistreatment-and-discrimination-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGlossier%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20workers%20reported%20discrimination%20and%20mistreatment%20under%20founder%20and%20former%20CEO%20Emily%20Weiss's%20tenure%20(Weiss%20apologized%2C%20too).%20Elizabeth%20Holmes%20lied%20to%20investors%20and%20risked%20lives%20(she%20apologized%2C%20and%20is%20serving%20an%2011-year%20prison%20sentence).%20Sandberg%20herself%20is%20facing%20new%20allegations%20of%20toxic%20behavior%3A%20A%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-meta-executive-sarah-wynn-williams-interview-careless-people-book-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ememoir%20by%20Sarah%20Wynn-Williams%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20policy%20director%20at%20Facebook%20(now%20Meta)%2C%20claims%20that%20Sandberg%20had%20a%20young%20assistant%20sleep%20in%20her%20lap%20and%20demanded%20the%20author%20join%20her%20in%20bed%20on%20a%20private%20jet.%20The%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BCareless%20People%2C%26quot%3B%20also%20highlights%20the%20ways%20women%20at%20Facebook%20felt%20leadership%20had%20failed%20them.%20Meta%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-employee-book-careless-people-sarah-wynn-williams-bestseller-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eslammed%20the%20book%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20inaccurate%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bmix%20of%20out-of-date%20and%20previously%20reported%20claims%20about%20the%20company%20and%20false%20accusations%20about%20our%20executives.%26quot%3B%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Sandberg's%20Lean%20In%20organization%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20memoir%2C%20but%20directed%20me%20to%20its%20website%20for%20information%20about%20ways%20Lean%20In%20sees%20itself%20as%20evolving%20to%20help%20women%20of%20all%20backgrounds%20navigate%20barriers%20and%20biases%20they%20may%20face%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20have%20proved%20they%20can%20behave%20just%20as%20badly%20as%20men%20%E2%80%94%20but%20even%20when%20they're%20on%20their%20best%20behavior%20or%20make%20minor%20missteps%2C%20they're%20hit%20with%20harsh%20criticism%20men%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20evade.%20A%202020%20study%20from%20the%20Stanford%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%20found%20that%20men%20are%20more%20valued%20than%20women%20when%20they%20%26quot%3Btake%20charge.%26quot%3B%20The%20%26quot%3Bfounder%20mode%2C%26quot%3B%20hands-on%2C%20direct%20style%20of%20management%20can%20backfire%20for%20women%20%E2%80%94%20as%20Airbnb%20CEO%20and%20founder%20mode%20proselytizer%20Brian%20Chesky%20posted%20on%20X%20last%20fall%3A%20%26quot%3BWomen%20founders%20have%20been%20reaching%20out%20to%20me%20over%20the%20past%2024%20hours%20about%20how%20they%20don't%20have%20permission%20to%20run%20their%20companies%20in%20Founder%20Mode%20the%20same%20way%20men%20can.%20This%20needs%20to%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20you%20have%20more%20women%2C%20they'll%20still%20assimilate%20to%20the%20workplace%20culture%20you%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Erika%20Lucas%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20StitchCrew%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20focused%20on%20fostering%20equitable%20entrepreneurship%2C%20and%20VEST%2C%20a%20women's%20peer%20network%20and%20investment%20fund.%20%26quot%3BWomen%20are%20being%20conditioned%20to%20fit%20into%20this%20meritocracy%2C%20or%20fit%20within%20these%20toxic%20systems%20because%20that's%20all%20we%20have.%26quot%3B%20As%20Cheryan%20puts%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bmasculine%20defaults%26quot%3B%20are%20diffuse%20in%20the%20workplace%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20men%20made%20companies%20in%20their%20image.%20The%20return%20of%20those%20defaults%20are%20pushing%20more%20women%20to%20ditch%20corporate%20America%20and%20go%20out%20on%20their%20own%2C%20says%20Lucas.%20%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20why%20we're%20seeing%20more%20women-led%20companies%20starting%20is%20because%20corporate%20America%20is%20not%20working%20for%20women.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20companies%20won't%20offer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-rto-five-days-tips-back-office-millennial-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ework-from-home%20policies%20or%20flexibility%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20working%20parents%20need%2C%20it%20can%20embolden%20people%20to%20become%20more%20entrepreneurial%20and%20build%20under%20their%20own%20terms.%20%26quot%3BOftentimes%20the%20easiest%20way%20to%20find%20that%20is%20to%20build%20it%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jaclyn%20Pascocello%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Fabrik%2C%20a%20networking%20space%20for%20people%20to%20grow%20their%20communities%2C%20noting%20that%20it's%20still%20not%20easy%20to%20launch%20a%20company.%20But%20in%20this%20climate%20of%20ascendant%20machoism%2C%20she%20says%2C%20she%20is%20seeing%20a%20collective%20of%20women%20coming%20together%20at%20Fabrik%20and%20starting%20to%20build%20companies%20to%20address%20issues%20sometimes%20ignored%20by%20men.%20Those%20can%20include%20solutions%20for%20women's%20health%20and%20caregiving.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20feels%20like%20there's%20a%20ton%20of%20women%20trying%20to%20lift%20each%20other%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20oversimplifying%20%26quot%3Bmasculine%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfeminine%26quot%3B%20traits%20to%20fit%20narrow%20boxes%20%26quot%3Bis%20doing%20everyone%20a%20disservice%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ashley%20Rose%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20cybersecurity%20firm%20Living%20Security.%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20find%20people%20that%20possess%20the%20traits%20that%20work%20well%20in%20your%20culture.%26quot%3B%20Similarly%2C%20the%20concept%20of%20DEI%20has%20been%20misrepresented%20and%20turned%20into%20a%20dirty%20acronym%20by%20the%20political%20right%2C%20says%20Virginia%20Cumberbatch%2C%20a%20global%20DEI%20strategist%20and%20consultant.%20While%20DEI%20implementation%20has%20been%20lacking%20and%20its%20results%20disappointing%20at%20some%20firms%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20for%20new%20and%20old%20companies%20to%20create%20initiatives%20to%20foster%20diversity%2C%20even%20in%20the%20current%20political%20climate.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20allowed%20DEI%20to%20be%20a%20catchall%20that's%20kind%20of%20lost%20its%20meaning%2C%26quot%3B%20Cumberbatch%20says.%20DEI%2C%20she%20says%2C%20shouldn't%20be%20thought%20of%20as%20a%20blanket%20fix.%20Equity%20looks%20different%20in%20the%20work%20of%20a%20university%20or%20an%20architecture%20firm.%20And%20companies%20that%20are%20serious%20about%20building%20diverse%2C%20equitable%2C%20and%20inclusive%20environments%20need%20to%20give%20authority%20to%20the%20people%20who%20work%20in%20it%20at%20a%20senior%20level.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20to%20be%20pervasive%20in%20every%20dimension%20of%20your%20organization%20or%20your%20brand%2C%20or%20it%20is%20just%20rhetoric%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20business%20case%20for%20stifling%20diversity.%20Many%20studies%20have%20found%20that%20having%20a%20diverse%20staff%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoca-cola-warns-negative-impact-dei-changes-filing-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egood%20for%20companies%20financially%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20benefits%20like%20extended%20parental%20leave%2C%20caregiving%20resources%2C%20and%20flexibility%20help%20with%20employee%20retention%20and%20burnout.%20And%20Big%20Tech%20businesses%20have%20ballooned%20in%20value%20while%20they%20publicly%20called%20for%20diversity%2C%20but%20they%20ride%20the%20tides%20of%20public%20opinion.%20Personalities%20that%20are%20power-obsessed%20often%20swing%20politically%20to%20hold%20onto%20their%20prestige.%20With%20that%20reality%20exposed%2C%20some%20women%20are%20changing%20their%20responses.%20Vanessa%20Jupe%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Leva%2C%20a%20platform%20to%20support%20new%20parents%2C%20says%20she%20became%20more%20politically%20active%20in%20the%202024%20election%20and%20supported%20Kamala%20Harris'%20campaign%20by%20canvassing%20her%20neighborhood%20and%20donating%20money.%20Some%20Facebook%20groups%20dedicated%20to%20campaigning%20for%20Harris%20have%20morphed%20into%20places%20of%20action%2C%20with%20members%20organizing%20to%20write%20letters%20and%20calling%20lawmakers%20to%20express%20frustration%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration.%20Escalating%20tactics%20could%20include%20strikes%2C%20sit-ins%2C%20picketing%2C%20and%20actions%20like%20the%20late%20February%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-blackout-boycott-protest-feb-28-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eeconomic%20blackout%3