Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20January%202023%2C%20Sankar%20has%20also%20been%20the%20founder%20of%200xPPL%2C%20a%20decentralized%20social%20network%20designed%20for%20crypto%20communities%2C%20as%20per%20his%20LinkedIn%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20his%20passion%20for%20programming%2C%20Sankar%20shares%20on%20LinkedIn%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20used%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20programming%20contests%3A%20I%20was%20ranked%20%231%20in%20India%20at%20TopCoder%20while%20in%20college%2C%20was%20a%20two-time%20Google%20Code%20Jam%20world%20finalist%2C%20and%20a%20two-time%20ACM%20ICPC%20world%20finalist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742800020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fqfsjiq9_prasanna-sankar_625x300_24_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwho-is-prasanna-sankar-all-about-rippling-co-founder-caught-in-custody-battle-with-wife-7997010%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20Prasanna%20Sankar%2C%20his%20wife%20has%20falsely%20accused%20him%20of%20rape%2C%20domestic%20violence%2C%20and%20kidnapping.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwho-is-prasanna-sankar-all-about-rippling-co-founder-caught-in-custody-battle-with-wife-7997010%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20is%20Fahim%20Khan%3F%20Arrested%20minority%20leader%20at%20heart%20of%20Nagpur%20violence%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742799951000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119412560%2Cimgsize-381338.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fnagpur%2Fwho-is-fahim-khan-arrested-minority-rights-leader-at-the-heart-of-nagpurs-violent-unrest%2Farticleshow%2F119411244.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fahim%20Khan%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20Minorities%20Democratic%20Party%2C%20is%20a%20key%20figure%20in%20the%20Nagpur%20riots%20investigation.%20He%20was%20arrested%20by%20Ganeshpeth%20police%20for%20allegedly%20inciting%20the%20Mahal%20riots.%20His%20political%20career%20is%20under%20scrutiny.%20The%20riots%20resulted%20in%20significant%20destruction%2C%20including%2070%20injuries%20and%20over%2040%20vehicles%20torched.%20Police%20have%20booked%20over%201%2C200%20individuals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20CITY%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Israel%20May%20Be%20Planning%20To%20Occupy%20Gaza%20Indefinitely%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20people%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20in%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20reached%20a%20new%20milestone%20over%20the%20weekend.%20More%20than%2050%2C000%20people%20have%20now%20died%2C%20including%2015%2C613%20children%2C%20according%20to%20figures%20released%20by%20Gaza's%20health%20ministry%20on%20Sunday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%20700%20Palestinians%20have%20lost%20their%20lives%20since%20last%20Tuesday%2C%20when%20Israel%20restarted%20lethal%20air%20strikes%20in%20Gaza%20last%20week.%20Both%20Israel%20and%20the%20US%20have%20blamed%20Hamas%20for%20the%20new%20offensive%2C%20which%20has%20ripped%20into%20a%20fragile%20ceasefire%20that%20had%20largely%20held%20since%20it%20came%20into%20effect%20in%20January.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20said%20the%20military%20was%20asked%20to%20take%20action%20against%20the%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%E2%80%9D%20group%20after%20its%20%26quot%3Brepeated%20refusal%20to%20release%20our%20hostages%26quot%3B%20as%20well%20as%20its%20rejection%20of%20US%20proposals.%20But%20many%20question%20the%20true%20intentions%20of%20Netanyahu.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20phase%20of%20the%20ceasefire%20ended%20on%20March%201.%20In%20the%20second%20phase%2C%20Hamas%20was%20to%20release%20the%20remaining%2059%20hostages%E2%80%9435%20of%20them%20believed%20to%20be%20dead%E2%80%94in%20exchange%20for%20more%20Palestinian%20prisoners%2C%20a%20lasting%20ceasefire%20and%20an%20Israeli%20withdrawal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Israel%20never%20started%20negotiations%20for%20the%20second%20phase.%20US%20envoy%20Steve%20Witkoff%20put%20forward%20his%20new%20%26quot%3Bbridging%20proposal%26quot%3B%20that%20would%20have%20extended%20the%20expired%20first%20phase.%20He%20proposed%20that%20more%20hostages%20would%20return%20home%20in%20exchange%20for%20more%20Palestinian%20prisoners.%20But%2C%20crucially%2C%20negotiations%20over%20a%20permanent%20end%20to%20the%20war%20would%20be%20delayed.%20That%20was%20not%20acceptable%20to%20Hamas%2C%20and%20Israel%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20ceasefire%20agreement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20New%20Israeli%20Offensive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHas%20Netanyahu's%20government%20restarted%20its%20bombing%20campaign%20because%20of%20Hamas%20refusing%20to%20free%20the%20remaining%20hostages%2C%20or%20is%20it%20due%20to%20issues%20he%20is%20facing%20at%20home%3F%C2%A0Is%20this%20move%20an%20attempt%20to%20implement%20a%20long-held%20agenda%20of%20the%20far-right%20in%20Israel%20to%20occupy%20Gaza%20permanently%2C%20reestablish%20Israeli%20settlements%20there%2C%20or%20even%20implement%20President%20Trump's%20plan%20to%20expel%20Palestinians%20from%20the%20territory%20and%20make%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Criviera%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20Friday%2C%20Israel's%20Defence%20Minister%2C%20Israel%20Katz%2C%20said%20he%20had%20instructed%20the%20military%20to%20seize%20additional%20areas%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20while%20issuing%20evacuation%20orders%20for%20Palestinian%20civilians%20in%20those%20areas%20to%20build%20up%20pressure%20on%20Hamas.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20Hamas%20terror%20organisation%20continues%20to%20refuse%20to%20release%20the%20hostages%2C%20I%20instructed%20the%20IDF%20to%20capture%20additional%20areas%2C%20evacuate%20the%20population%2C%20and%20expand%20the%20security%20zone%20around%20Gaza%20for%20the%20protection%20of%20Israeli%20communities%20and%20IDF%20soldiers%2C%20through%20a%20permanent%20hold%20of%20the%20area%20by%20Israel%E2%80%A6As%20long%20as%20Hamas%20continues%20its%20refusal%2C%20it%20will%20lose%20more%20and%20more%20land%20that%20will%20be%20added%20to%20Israel%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20looks%20at%20Katz's%20statement%20along%20with%20reports%20in%20the%20Israeli%20media%2C%20the%20Netanyahu%20government's%20plan%20for%20Gaza%20appears%20to%20emerge.%20Reports%20in%20the%20Israel%20media%20say%20the%20military%20chief%2C%20Eyal%20Zamir%2C%20is%20preparing%20for%20a%20full-scale%20ground%20offensive%20to%20reinstate%20military%20control%20in%20Gaza.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20seems%20that%20Israel%20is%20currently%20creating%20a%20smokescreen%20around%20the%20government%20and%20military's%20true%20intentions.%20While%20waiting%20for%20possible%20updates%20in%20negotiations%2C%20which%20are%20uncertain%2C%20preparations%20are%20underway%20for%20a%20large-scale%20operation%20to%20occupy%20Gaza%20and%20restore%20full%20Israeli%20control%2C%E2%80%9D%20writes%20commentator%20Amos%20Hartel%20in%20Haaretz%20newspaper.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20will%20occur%20while%20the%20far-right%20factions%20in%20the%20government%20push%20for%20the%20return%20of%20settlements%20and%20the%20forced%20expulsion%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20to%20be%20presented%20as%20%E2%80%98voluntary%20migration'%2C%20with%20backing%20from%20Donald%20Trump%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20Israeli%20Settlements%20Return%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20Israel's%20far-right%20would%20like%20the%20reported%20plan%20to%20be%20implemented.%20They%20have%20been%20demanding%20for%20months%20that%20the%20Israeli%20settlements%20come%20back%20to%20Gaza%20(Israel%20had%20settlements%20in%20Gaza%20until%202005%2C%20which%20were%20removed%20after%20the%20government%20decided%20to%20pull%20back).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20most%20analysts%20and%20commentators%20in%20Israel%20thought%20resettling%20Gaza%20was%20far-fetched.%20But%20not%20anymore.%20In%20October%2C%20two%20senior%20far-right%20Cabinet%20ministers%2C%20six%20lawmakers%20from%20Netanyahu's%20Likud%20party%20and%20several%20of%20his%20party's%20local%20leaders%20from%20across%20Israel%20attended%20a%20pro-settlement%20rally%2C%20where%20demands%20were%20raised%20for%20creating%20Israeli%20settlements%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20Israeli%20public%20is%20ready%20for%20such%20a%20plan%2C%20or%20even%20for%20a%20permanent%20occupation%20of%20Gaza.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20it%20is%20unlikely%20to%20make%20them%20more%20secure.%20Gazans%20are%20also%20not%20willing%20to%20leave%20the%20territory%20despite%20their%20unprecedented%20hardships%20since%20the%20Hamas-Israel%20war.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnPalestinians%20can't%20forget%20the%20%E2%80%9CNakba%E2%80%9D%20of%201948%2C%20in%20which%2C%20following%20the%20founding%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%2C%20about%20half%20of%20the%20civilians%20residing%20in%20Palestine%20were%20forced%20to%20leave%20their%20homes%20and%20never%20allowed%20to%20return.%20Many%20settled%20in%20Gaza.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrowing%20Protests%20Against%20The%20Plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20his%20plan%2C%20Trump%20has%20suggested%20that%20Arab%20countries%E2%80%94Egypt%20and%20Jordan%2C%20in%20particular%E2%80%94absorb%20the%20displaced%20population%2C%20while%20the%20United%20States%20would%20%E2%80%9Cown%E2%80%9D%20the%20seaside%20territory.%20Arabs%20and%20even%20America's%20allies%20denounced%20the%20plan%2C%20which%20has%20been%20condemned%20as%20%E2%80%98ethnic%20cleansing'%20by%20global%20human%20rights%20groups.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Israel%20itself%2C%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20across%20Israel%20have%20been%20staging%20protests%20against%20Netanyahu%20since%20last%20week.%20Protesters%20and%20his%20other%20critics%20have%20accused%20him%20of%20undermining%20democracy%20and%20restarting%20the%20war%20simply%20to%20divert%20attention%20from%20the%20political%20and%20legal%20problems%20he%20has%20been%20facing%2C%20thus%20jeopardising%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20remaining%20hostages.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20immediate%20trigger%20for%20protests%20was%20Netanyahu's%20sacking%20of%20Ronen%20Bar%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Israel's%20internal%20security%20agency%2C%20Shin%20Bet%20(though%20this%20was%20later%20put%20on%20hold%20by%20a%20court%20while%20judges%20examined%20the%20evidence).%20The%20resumption%20of%20military%20action%20in%20Gaza%20fuelled%20their%20anger%20further.%20Netanyahu%20has%20accused%20Bar%20of%20failing%20to%20prevent%20the%20Hamas%20attacks%20on%20October%207%2C%202023%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%201%2C200%20Israeli%20deaths%20and%20the%20abduction%20of%20more%20than%20250%20other%20Israelis%2C%20which%20triggered%20the%20ongoing%20Israel-Hamas%20war.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20worst%20attack%20in%20Israel's%20history%2C%20sparking%20outrage%20not%20only%20in%20the%20country%20but%20across%20the%20globe.%20Ironically%20though%2C%20Netanyahu%20himself%20has%20not%20taken%20any%20responsibility%20for%20the%20horrific%20terrorist%20attack%2C%20which%20happened%20under%20his%20watch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENetanyahu's%20Troubles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20Israeli%20prime%20minister%20before%20Netanyahu%20has%20ever%20fired%20the%20head%20of%20a%20security%20agency%20during%20a%20war.%20His%20critics%20argue%20that%20the%20real%20reason%20behind%20the%20move%20appears%20to%20be%20investigations%20launched%20by%20Shin%20Bet%20against%20officials%20close%20to%20Netanyahu.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20is%20probing%20a%20spokesperson%20who%20allegedly%20leaked%20to%20a%20German%20news%20outlet%20classified%20documents%20that%20appeared%20to%20give%20the%20prime%20minister%20political%20cover%20in%20ceasefire%20negotiations.%20Shin%20Bet%20is%20also%20looking%20into%20claims%20that%20Qatar%20reportedly%20hired%20close%20Netanyahu%20aides%20to%20launch%20a%20public%20relations%20campaign%20in%20Israel.%20Qatar%20had%20sent%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20cash%20to%20Gaza%2C%20with%20Netanyahu's%20approval.%20The%20assumption%20is%20that%20this%20money%20reached%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetanyahu's%20critics%20also%20point%20to%20his%20attempts%20to%20sack%20his%20Attorney%20General%2C%20Gali%20Baharav-Miara%2C%20who%20had%20said%20that%20the%20Israeli%20PM%20needed%20to%20clarify%20the%20legal%20basis%20for%20his%20decision%20to%20remove%20Bar%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20role%20of%20the%20Shin%20Bet%20is%20not%20to%20serve%20the%20personal%20trust%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20the%20Israeli%20cabinet%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20against%20Gali%20Baharav-Miara%2C%20in%20a%20move%20designed%20to%20hasten%20her%20dismissal.%20In%20response%2C%20she%20said%20the%20government%20was%20seeking%20to%20place%20itself%20above%20the%20law%20and%20operate%20without%20checks%20and%20balances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProtesters%20are%20also%20concerned%20about%20judicial%20reforms%20that%20would%20introduce%20more%20political%20appointees%20to%20committees%20selecting%20judges.%20Netanyahu%20is%20already%20undergoing%20a%20corruption%20trial%2C%20for%20which%20he%20has%20been%20appearing%20in%20court.%20He%20faces%20charges%20related%20to%20fraud%2C%20bribery%20and%20breach%20of%20trust%2C%20though%20he%20alleges%20that%20they%20are%20politically%20motivated%20and%20fabricated%20by%20his%20opponents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Playbook%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20a%20leaf%20out%20of%20Trump's%20book%2C%20a%20defiant%20Netanyahu%20says%20there%20has%20been%20a%20conspiracy%20against%20him%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98leftist%20deep%20state'%2C%20just%20as%20Trump%20was%20being%20targeted%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9CIn%20America%20and%20in%20Israel%2C%20when%20a%20strong%20rightwing%20leader%20wins%20an%20election%2C%20the%20leftist%20deep%20state%20weaponises%20the%20justice%20system%20to%20thwart%20the%20people's%20will.%20They%20won't%20win%20in%20either%20place!%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%20last%20week.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnBut%20opinion%20polls%20show%20Netanyahu%20is%20now%20deeply%20unpopular%20in%20his%20country%20and%20might%20lose%20an%20election%20if%20it%20takes%20place%20now.%20He%20thus%20relies%20even%20more%20on%20far-right%20partners%20for%20his%20government%20to%20survive%20now.%20This%20could%20be%20one%20reason%20for%20his%20trying%20to%20appease%20them%20regarding%20the%20Gaza%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeft%20In%20The%20Lurch%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20brutal%20military%20response%20to%20the%20October%207%20attacks%20by%20Hamas%20has%20resulted%20in%20devastating%20consequences%20not%20only%20for%20the%20militant%20group%20but%20also%20for%20Gaza's%20general%20population.%20Most%20of%20the%20leaders%20of%20Hamas%20and%20its%20ally%2C%20the%20Lebanese%20militant%20group%20Hezbollah%2C%20have%20been%20killed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20other%20enemies%2C%20like%20Yemen-based%20Houthis%20and%20its%20sponsor%20Iran%2C%20are%20now%20much%20weakened.%20The%20regime%20change%20in%20Syria%20has%20also%20given%20a%20strategic%20advantage%20to%20the%20country.%20So%2C%20the%20parties%20supporting%20Hamas%20are%20either%20gone%20or%20are%20hardly%20able%20to%20threaten%20Israel%20anymore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Trump%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Netanyahu%20could%20not%20find%20a%20better%20ally%20in%20America.%20In%20contrast%20to%20his%20desperate%20attempts%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Trump%20doesn't%20seem%20keen%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20fighting%20in%20Gaza.%20Although%20he%20did%20pressure%20Netanyahu%20to%20agree%20on%20a%20ceasefire%20deal%20with%20Hamas%20in%20January%2C%20his%20support%20for%20Israel's%20new%20offensive%20suggests%20that%20he%20may%20still%20be%20hoping%20for%20his%20Gaza%20Riviera%20plan%20to%20succeed%2C%20regardless%20of%20what%20this%20could%20mean%20for%20Gaza's%20civilians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20don't%20have%20powerful%20backers%2C%20such%20as%20the%20European%20governments%20that%20have%20vowed%20to%20help%20another%20embattled%20population%2C%20the%20Ukrainians%2C%20even%20if%20the%20US%20abandons%20them.%20Even%20Arab%20governments%2C%20including%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20host%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20ceasefire%20talks%20and%20the%20most%20powerful%20Arab%20nation%2C%20have%20not%20provided%20such%20support%20to%20the%20Palestinians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Naresh%20Kaushik%20is%20a%20former%20editor%20at%20the%20Associated%20Press%20and%20BBC%20News%20and%20is%20based%20in%20London)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742799840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fp2hnijko_israel-attacks-gaza_625x300_19_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fis-israel-planning-to-occupy-gaza-indefinitely-7996988%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20one%20looks%20at%20Katz's%20statement%20along%20with%20reports%20in%20the%20Israeli%20media%2C%20the%20Netanyahu%20government's%20plan%20for%20Gaza%20appears%20to%20emerge.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fis-israel-planning-to-occupy-gaza-indefinitely-7996988%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%2