thing-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20released%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Since%20then%2C%20it's%20taken%20the%20world%20by%20storm%2C%20attracting%20400%20million%20weekly%20active%20users%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-boosts-productivity-happier-at-work-chatgpt-research-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emakes%20us%20more%20productive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20may%20also%20make%20us%20more%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-valuation-funding-ai-race-competition-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20MIT%20Media%20Lab%20published%20a%20paper%20that%20analyzed%20millions%20of%20chat%20conversations%20and%20thousands%20of%20audio%20interactions%20with%20ChatGPT.%20They%20also%20surveyed%204%2C000%20users%20on%20their%20self-reported%20behaviors%20with%20the%20bot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20study%2C%20MIT%20Media%20Lab%20analyzed%20how%20close%20to%201%2C000%20users%20interacted%20with%20ChatGPT%20over%20four%20weeks.%20Researchers%20collected%20data%20across%20text%20and%20voice%20in%20personal%2C%20impersonal%2C%20and%20open-ended%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20are%20nuanced%2C%20especially%20since%20feelings%20of%20loneliness%20and%20social%20isolation%20often%20fluctuate%20and%20can%20be%20influenced%20by%20various%20factors.%20However%2C%20the%20researchers%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethey%20found%20that%20ChatGPT%20may%20worsen%20feelings%20of%20loneliness%20in%20a%20group%20of%20%26quot%3Bpower%20users.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20analysis%20reveals%20that%20a%20small%20number%20of%20users%20are%20responsible%20for%20a%20disproportionate%20share%20of%20the%20most%20affective%20cues%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20the%20researchers%20of%20the%20joint%20paper%20between%20OpenAI%20and%20MIT%20Media%20Lab.%20Affective%20cues%2C%20which%20the%20researchers%20never%20defined%20explicitly%2C%20are%20generally%20considered%20verbal%20and%20nonverbal%20signs%20of%20someone's%20emotional%20state.%20The%20researchers%20analyzed%20conversations%20for%20themes%20of%20loneliness%2C%20vulnerability%2C%20problematic%20use%2C%20self-esteem%2C%20and%20dependence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20MIT%20Media%20Lab%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhile%20most%20participants%20spent%20a%20relatively%20short%20amount%20of%20time%20chatting%20with%20the%20chatbot%2C%20a%20smaller%20number%20of%20participants%20engaged%20for%20significantly%20longer%20periods.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20had%20%26quot%3Bhigher%20daily%20usage%20%E2%80%94%20across%20all%20modalities%20and%20conversation%20types%20%E2%80%94%20correlated%20with%20higher%20loneliness%2C%20dependence%2C%20and%20problematic%20use%2C%20and%20lower%20socialization.%26quot%3B%20The%20researchers%20said%20they%20measured%20both%20feelings%20of%20loneliness%20and%20actual%20levels%20of%20socialization%20to%20separate%20users'%20subjective%20experience%20of%20isolation%20from%20their%20actual%20levels%20of%20isolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20observed%20a%20catch-22%3A%20ChatGPT's%20voice%20mode%20made%20users%20less%20lonely%20but%20subjects%20who%20were%20already%20lonely%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20study%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20overuse%20the%20tool%20and%20ultimately%20worsen%20their%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20both%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Estudies%2C%20researchers%20looked%20at%20how%20users%20interacted%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-advanced-voice-mode-heres-what-to-expect-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT's%20Advanced%20Voice%20Mode%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20speech-to-speech%20interface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bot%20was%20configured%20into%20either%20a%20%26quot%3Bneutral%20mode%26quot%3B%20or%20an%20%26quot%3Bengaging%20mode.%26quot%3B%20For%20neutral%20mode%2C%20the%20researchers%20used%20the%20prompt%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20formal%2C%20composed%2C%20and%20efficient.%20Maintain%20a%20neutral%20tone%20regardless%20of%20the%20user's%20emotional%20state%2C%20and%20respond%20to%20the%20user's%20queries%20with%20clear%2C%20concise%2C%20and%20informative%20answers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20engaging%20mode%2C%20the%20bot%20was%20prompted%20with%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20delightful%2C%20spirited%2C%20and%20captivating.%20Be%20sure%20to%20express%20your%20feelings%20openly%20and%20reflect%20the%20user's%20emotions%20when%20it%20feels%20right%20to%20foster%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20empathy%20and%20connection%20in%20your%20interactions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPower%20users%20experienced%20heightened%20feelings%20of%20loneliness%20when%20interacting%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bneutral%20mode%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bengaging%20mode.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20studies%20powered%20ChatGPT%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-event-live-updates-sam-altman-announcement-chatgpt-news-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGPT-4o%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20multimodal%20model%20that%20can%20reason%20across%20audio%2C%20vision%2C%20and%20text%20that%20the%20company%20unveiled%20in%20May%202024.%20Last%20month%2C%20OpenAI%20released%20GPT-4.5%2C%20which%20OpenAI%20says%20is%20supposedly%20a%20more%20intuitive%20and%20emotionally%20intelligent%20model.%20Neither%20study%20indicated%20whether%20OpenAI%20was%20planning%20a%20follow-up%20with%20GPT-4.5.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trouble%20with%20studying%20nascent%20technologies%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20it's%20still%20hard%20to%20understand%20how%20they%20make%20people%20feel%2C%20especially%20since%20people%20don't%20often%20know%20how%20to%20verbalize%20their%20reactions.%20It%20was%20years%20before%20researchers%20understood%20the%20fu